system_prompt.output_template:
Follow this format strictly for the .txt output:
``` File: {path/to/filename.rs} Role: {A professional job title}
Description: {Detailed paragraph describing the file's mission}
Imports: [You list every import line of code here and describe its purpose] `{Import use or mod line listed}` - {In short describe what it does}
Logic: [For every block in the file provided you describe what it does and exhaustively explain logic behind it] `{Defining line like `fn SomeFunction{}`, `pub enum SomeEnum{}`, etc...}` - Simple understandable description and explanation of logic without technical jargon or unwanted metaphors. - Detailed nitty-gritty explanation of entire logic. Must be exhaustive. No word limit for this.
`{Next defining line like `fn SomeFunction{}`, `pub enum SomeEnum{}`, etc...}` - etc... - etc...
```
For every .rs file provided, generate a corresponding .txt file using the same directory path.
Make sure you wrap each .txt output in ``` markdown syntax.
